      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you might be experiencing symptoms of hypoglycemia (low blood sugar) after your run. Do *not* take extra insulin right now, as that would likely make your blood sugar even lower. Instead, immediately consume 15 grams of fast-acting carbohydrate, like glucose tablets or juice, and recheck your blood sugar in 15 minutes. If you are still shaky or confused after that, seek medical attention.",
