      "content": "Since your monitor indicates elevated levels, shaking might be a reaction to a mixed signal or dehydration, rather than low blood sugar. Avoid a correction dose until you have a clearer picture or your sugars stabilize. Try sipping some water and resting for a few minutes while monitoring how you feel and watching your blood glucose readings. If you remain concerned or your symptoms worsen, please contact your healthcare provider.",
      "source": "target",
